## Notes on formulas & targets

* **BHH bound (unit square):** (\mathbb{E}[L^*]\approx \beta\sqrt{n}), (\beta\simeq 0.712). At (n=500), ( \beta\sqrt{500} \approx 15.9\text{–}16.2). We stop at (1.01\times) that to prioritize quality without over-searching.
* **2-opt gain (double):** (\Delta_d = d(i,i')+d(j,j')-d(i,j)-d(i',j')); accept if (\Delta_d>0).
* **Weight update:** (\Delta w = \lambda,[\exp(\Delta/L)-1]), computed on double scale.

## What to watch in logs

* “Early stop: reached BHH threshold (…)”
* “Time guard reached (…)”
* Iteration logs each 100 restarts still show phase timings and current double length.

If you want to drive length even lower, next knobs (safe): raise `K` to 64 and allow `double-bridge` kicks between restarts; but with the current improvements, you should already see a solid drop toward ~16.5 without blowing time.
